There ain‚Äôt no gold
In this river
That I‚Äôve been washing my hands in forever
I know there is hope
In these waters
But I can‚Äôt bring myself to swim

In this silence baby let me in
 
Go easy on me baby
I was still a child
Didn‚Äôt get the chance to 
Feel the world around me
I had no time to choose
What I chose to do
So go easy on me
 
There ain‚Äôt no room 
For things to change
When we are both so deeply 
Stuck in our ways
You can‚Äôt deny how hard I have tried
I changed who I was
To put you both first
But now I give up 
 
I had good intentions
And the highest hopes
But I know right now
It probably doesn‚Äôt even show
